description:
Are you someone who loves connecting with people, discovering opportunities, and making things happen? We’re looking for a curious, energetic Business Developer to help us grow in Sweden.



At IXON, we connect machines with their builders. We are at the forefront of revolutionising the way machines are connected, monitored and controlled. By providing an end-to-end solution, consisting of our in-house developed cloud platform and connectivity hardware, we empower machine builders with the tools and technology to stay future-proof and transform the way they do business. All with one goal: more efficient production with the lowest possible impact on the world.  





**This is what energises you**


As Business Developer Sweden, you’ll be part of our Nordics team and play a key role in expanding our presence across the Swedish market. You’ll focus on business development, identifying new opportunities, building long-term relationships, and turning prospects into clients. It is your mission to help Swedish machine builders to further improve their service by showing them what is possible with the IXON platform.



On a daily basis, you will be involved in the following activities:

* Identifying and developing new business opportunities with machine builders in Sweden;
* Executing the full sales cycle: from prospecting and first contact to closing deals;
* Building a strong network of prospects and industry connections;
* Collaborating closely with Marketing, Sales Support, and Solution Engineers to deliver the best customer experience;
* Providing market insights and feedback to continuously improve our go-to-market strategy in Sweden.

 **This makes you successful**


You’re entrepreneurial, curious, and ready to make your mark in a recently entered region. You thrive on connecting with people and turning conversations into commercial success. You enjoy working independently but also value being part of an international, fast-paced team.



In addition, it would also be nice if you identify with the following points:

* 2–5 years of experience in a commercial or business development role (B2B);
* Fluent in Swedish and English;
* Strong communication and relationship-building skills;
* Eagerness to learn and grow, with a hands-on mentality;
* Affinity with industrial automation, cloud solutions or mechanical engineering is a big plus;
* You are based in Sweden (preferably in the region: Västra Götaland, Halland or Jönköping/Småland) and willing to travel within the region by car.

**Here’s what we offer you**


At IXON, you will join an international and dynamic environment, where you can make an immediate impact and grow rapidly. Together with your colleagues, you will contribute to the development of our innovative organisation. You get the opportunity to unlock your potential in a dynamic work environment where autonomy, a vibrant work culture, personal growth and meaningful contributions in industrial automation awaits you. Of course, we reward your dedication with a competitive salary and excellent secondary benefits.

 **Ready to dive in?**


Start your journey and connect with IXON! Applying is quick and easy, just click the button below.



Need more details? Reach out to our recruiter, Joey van Elsen, by calling +31628819109 or send an email to careers@ixon.cloud.

 *Agency interest in this vacancy is not desired.*
